\u00f8rgen de Mylius\"/>}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|1982}}\n|Hans Otto Bisgaard ||{{center|<ref name=\"J\u00f8rgen de Mylius\"/>}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|1983}}\n|rowspan=\"11\"|Bent Henius ||{{center|<ref name=\"J\u00f8rgen de Mylius\"/>}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|1984}}\n|{{center|<ref name=\"J\u00f8rgen de Mylius\"/>}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|1985}}\n|{{center|<ref name=\"J\u00f8rgen de Mylius\"/>}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|1986}}\n|{{center|<ref name=\"J\u00f8rgen de Mylius\"/>}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|1987}}\n|{{center|<ref name=\"J\u00f8rgen de Mylius\"/>}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|1988}}\n|{{center|<ref name=\"J\u00f8rgen de Mylius\"/>}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|1989}}\n|{{center|<ref name=\"J\u00f8rgen de Mylius\"/>}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|1990}}\n|{{center|<ref name=\"J\u00f8rgen de Mylius\"/>}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|1991}}\n|Camilla Miehe-Renard ||{{center|<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0313378/fullcredits?ref_=tt_cl_sm#cast Eurovision Song Contest 1991]. [[Internet Movie Database]]. Retrieved 27 July 2013.</ref>}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|1992}}\n|rowspan=\"7\"|J\u00f8rgen de Mylius ||{{center|<ref name=\"J\u00f8rgen de Mylius\"/>}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|1993}}\n|{{center|<ref name=\"J\u00f8rgen de Mylius\"/>}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|1994}}\n|{{N/A|Did not participate}} ||{{center|<ref name=\"J\u00f8rgen de Mylius\"/>}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|1995}}\n|Bent Henius ||{{center|<ref name=\"J\u00f8rgen de Mylius\"/>}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|1996}}\n|{{N/A|Did not participate}} ||{{center|<ref name=\"J\u00f8rgen de Mylius\"/>}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|1997}}\n|Bent Henius ||{{center|<ref name=\"J\u00f8rgen de Mylius\"/>}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|1998}}\n|{{N/A|Did not participate}} ||{{center|<ref name=\"J\u00f8rgen de Mylius\"/>}}\n|- \n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|1999}}\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Keld Heick]] ||Kirsten Siggaard ||{{center|<ref name=\"Keld Heick\">{{cite web|title=Keld Heick|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1175639/|work=Filmography|publisher=[[Internet Movie Database]]|accessdate=15 July 2013}}</ref>}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2000}}\n|[[Michael Teschl]] ||{{center|<ref name=\"Keld Heick\"/>}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2001}}\n|Hans Otto Bisgaard and Hilda Heick ||[[Gry Johansen]] ||{{center|<ref name=\"Hans Otto Bisgaard\">{{cite web|title=Hans Otto Bisgaard|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1188662/|work=Filmography|publisher=[[Internet Movie Database]]|accessdate=15 July 2013}}</ref>}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2002}}\n|Keld Heick ||Signe Svendsen ||{{center|<ref name=\"Keld Heick\"/>}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2003}}\n|rowspan=\"3\"|J\u00f8rgen de Mylius ||{{N/A|Did not participate}} ||{{center|<ref name=\"J\u00f8rgen de Mylius\"/>}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2004}}\n|[[Camilla Ottesen]] ||{{center|<ref name=\"J\u00f8rgen de Mylius\"/>}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2005}}\n|Gry Johansen ||{{center|<ref name=\"J\u00f8rgen de Mylius\"/>}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2006}}\n|[[Mads Vangs\u00f8]] and [[Adam Duv\u00e5 Hall]] ||J\u00f8rgen de Mylius ||{{center|<ref name=\"J\u00f8rgen de Mylius\"/>}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2007}}\n|[[S\u00f8ren Nystr\u00f8m Rasted]] and [[Adam Duv\u00e5 Hall]] ||[[Susanne Georgi]] ||\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2008}}\n|rowspan=\"3\"|Nicolaj Molbech ||Maria Montell ||\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2009}}\n|[[Felix Smith]] ||\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2010}}\n|[[Bryan Rice]] ||\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2011}}\n|rowspan=\"9\"|[[Ole T\u00f8pholm]] ||[[Lise R\u00f8nne]] ||\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2012}}\n|[[Louise Wolff]] ||\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2013}}\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Sofie Lassen-Kahlke]] ||\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2014}}\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2015}}\n|[[Basim (singer)|Basim]] ||\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2016}}\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Ulla Essendrop]] ||\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2017}}\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2018}}\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2019}}\n|[[Rasmussen (singer)|Rasmussen]] ||\n|}\n\n===Conductors===\nAll conductors are Danish except those marked with a flag.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://andtheconductoris.eu/|title=And the conductor is...|website=andtheconductoris.eu|accessdate=5 January 2020}}</ref>\n{{Div col|content=\n* Kai Mortensen ({{Escyr|1957}}\u2013{{Escyr|1964}}) (musical director in {{Escyr|1964}})\n* Arne Lamberth ({{Escyr|1965}}\u2013{{Escyr|1966}})\n* Helmer Olsen ({{Escyr|1978}})\n* Allan Botchinsky ({{Escyr|1979}}\u2013{{Escyr|1983}})\n* Henrik Krogsg\u00e5rd ({{Escyr|1984}}, {{Escyr|1987}}\u2013{{Escyr|1992}})\n* Wolfgang K\u00e4fer ({{Escyr|1985}})\n* {{flagicon|Norway}} [[Egil Monn-Iversen]] ({{Escyr|1986}})\n* {{flagicon|France}} Beno\u00eet Kaufman ({{Escyr|1989}})\n* {{flagicon|Norway}} George Keller ({{Escyr|1993}})\n* Frede Ewert ({{Escyr|1995}})\n* Jan Gl\u00e6sel ({{Escyr|1997}})\n|colwidth=\n30em\n}}\n\nHenrik Krogsg\u00e5rd had conducted half of the 1989 entry before he joined [[Birthe Kj\u00e6r]] on the stage. Beno\u00eet Kaufman came and conducted the song until the end.\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery class=\"center\">\nImage:Birthe Wilke & Gustav Winckler.jpg|[[Birthe Wilke]] and [[Gustav Winckler]] in Frankfurt ([[Eurovision Song Contest 1957|1957]])\nImage:Eurovision Song Contest 1958 - Raquel Rastenni.png|[[Raquel Rastenni]] in Hilversum ([[Eurovision Song Contest 1958|1958]])\nImage:J\u00f8rgen & Grethe Ingmann.jpg|[[Grethe Ingmann|Grethe]] and [[J\u00f8rgen Ingmann]] ([[Eurovision Song Contest 1963|1963]])\nImage:ESC 2007 Denmark - DQ - Drama Queen.jpg|[[DQ (artist)|DQ]] at [[Helsinki]] ([[Eurovision Song Contest 2007|2007]])\nImage:Simon Mathew, Denmark, Eurovision 2008.jpg|[[Simon Mathew]] at [[Belgrade]] ([[Eurovision Song Contest 2008|2008]])\nimage:Christina Chan\u00e9e 01.JPG|[[Christina Chan\u00e9e|Chan\u00e9e]] & [[Tomas N'evergreen|N'evergreen]] at [[Oslo]] ([[Eurovision Song Contest 2010|2010]])\nImage:Denmark at ESC 2011.jpg|[[A Friend in London]] at [[D\u00fcsseldorf]] ([[