op ten non-[[Eurovision Song Contest#Big Four and Big Five|Big Four]] countries from the previous year along with the Big Four automatically qualified for the Grand Final without having to compete in semi-finals. For example, if Germany and France placed inside the top ten, the 11th and 12th spots were advanced to next year's Grand Final along with all countries ranked in the top ten.}}\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2007}}\n|[[DQ (singer)|DQ]]\n|English\n|\"[[Drama Queen (DQ song)|Drama Queen]]\"\n|colspan=\"2\" {{N/A|Failed to qualify}}\n|align=center|19\n|align=center|45\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2008}}\n|[[Simon Mathew]]\n|English\n|\"[[All Night Long (Simon Mathew song)|All Night Long]]\"\n|align=center|15\n|align=center|60\n|bgcolor=\"#C96\" align=center|3\n|bgcolor=\"#C96\" align=center|112\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2009}}\n|[[Niels Brinck]]\n|English\n|\"[[Believe Again (Niels Brinck song)|Believe Again]]\"\n|align=center|13\n|align=center|74\n|align=center|8\n|align=center|69\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2010}}\n|[[Christina Chan\u00e9e|Chan\u00e9e]] & [[Tomas N'evergreen|N'evergreen]]\n|English\n|\"[[In a Moment Like This]]\"\n|align=center|4\n|align=center|149\n|align=center|5\n|align=center|101\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2011}}\n|[[A Friend in London]]\n|English\n|\"[[New Tomorrow]]\"\n|align=center|5\n|align=center|134\n|bgcolor=\"silver\" align=center|2\n|bgcolor=\"silver\" align=center|135\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2012}}\n|[[Soluna Samay]]\n|English\n|\"[[Should've Known Better (Soluna Samay song)|Should've Known Better]]\"\n|align=center|23\n|align=center|21\n|align=center|9\n|align=center|63\n|-bgcolor=\"gold\"\n!{{Escyr|2013}}\n|[[Emmelie de Forest]]\n|English\n|\"[[Only Teardrops]]\"\n|align=center|1\n|align=center|281\n|align=center|1\n|align=center|167\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2014}}\n|[[Basim (singer)|Basim]] \n|English\n|\"[[Clich\u00e9 Love Song]]\"\n|align=center|9 \n|align=center|74\n|colspan=\"2\" data-sort-value=\"-9999\" {{N/A|Host country}}{{efn|name=note3|If a country had won the previous year, they did not have to compete i