-natalie-cassidy-35th-anniversary-plans/|title=EastEnders star Natalie Cassidy teases \"exciting\" 35th anniversary year|first=Dan|last=Seddon|work=Digital Spy|date=29 December 2019|publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |accessdate=8 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=2|'''21'''\n|The BBC announces that its consumer affairs programme ''[[Watchdog (TV programme)|Watchdog]]'' will be subsumed into ''[[The One Show]]'' from Spring 2020.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-51584666 |title=BBC to make Watchdog part of The One Show |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=21 February 2020 |accessdate=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[June Brown]] makes her final onscreen appearance in ''[[EastEnders]]'' as [[Dot Cotton]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-51582573|title=Dot Cotton: Actress June Brown says she has left EastEnders 'for good'|publisher=BBC News|date=21 February 2020|accessdate=21 February 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|'''22'''\n|''[[Ant & Dec's Saturday Night Takeaway]]'' returns to ITV for a new series. The first episode attracts 87 complaints to Ofcom following a raunchy performance by the [[Pussycat Dolls]].<ref>{{cite news|first=Simon |last=Duke |url=https://www.chroniclelive.co.uk/news/tv/pussycat-dolls-saturday-night-takeaway-17802899 |title=Pussycat Dolls' 'censored' Saturday Night Takeaway performance sparks Ofcom complaints |newspaper=Metro |date=24 February 2020 |accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|'''23'''\n|[[Finn Tapp]] and Paige Turley win [[Love Island (2015 TV series, series 6)|series six]] of ''Love Island''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-51584507 |title=Love Island: Tributes paid to Caroline Flack as winners are crowned |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=23 February 2020 |accessdate=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|'''26'''\n|ITV announces a shakeup of its weekend Breakfast schedule that will see the launch of two new programmes. [[Kate Garraway]] will present