g it the second-highest overnight viewership for the night after ''[[Emmerdale]]'' with an audience of 5 million.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.doctorwhonews.net/2020/01/spyfall-overnight-viewing-figures.html |title=Spyfall \u2013 Overnight Viewing Figures |work=Doctor Who News |last=Marcus |date=2 January 2020 |accessdate=2 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Miranda Hart]] is reunited with the cast of her eponymous sitcom, ''[[Miranda (TV series)|Miranda]]'' to celebrate its tenth anniversary in a special show recorded at the [[London Palladium]].<ref>{{cite news|first=Deepika |last=Rajani |url=https://inews.co.uk/culture/television/miranda-christmas-special-cast-2019-my-such-fun-celebration-bbc-one-when-guests-miranda-hart-1352252 |title=Miranda Christmas special cast: when is My Such Fun Celebration on BBC One, and the full line-up joining Miranda Hart |publisher=inews |date=1 January 2020 |accessdate=4 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[BBC One]] airs ''[[Craig David]] Rocks Big Ben Live'' to welcome in the New Year.<ref>{{cite news|first=Parwinder |last=Sandhu |url=https://www.ibtimes.sg/craig-david-steals-thunder-big-ben-live-36898 |title=Craig David steals the thunder on Big Ben Live |publisher=International Business Times |date=1 January 2020 |accessdate=2 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Dracula (2020 TV series)|Dracula]]'', a new three-part take on the [[Bram Stoker]] [[Dracula|novel of the same name]], begins airing on BBC One.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-50972189 |title=Dracula: Critics applaud 'energetic and fun' revival of vampire classic |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=2 January 2020 |accessdate=4 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=2|'''2'''\n|Figures released by the [[Broadcasters' Audience Research Board]] (BARB) indicate the 2019 Christmas special of ''[[Gavin & Stacey]]'' to be the most viewed scripted television programme of the 2010s, with an audience of 17.1 million. Only sporting events and the [[The X Factor (British series 7)|2010 series]] of ''[[The X Factor (British TV series)|The X Factor]]'' were seen by more viewers.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-50975665 |title=Gavin and Stacey Christmas special is most-watched TV comedy for 17 years |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=2 January 2020 |accessdate=2 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|The actress [[Amanda Henderson]] appears as a contestant on ''[[Celebrity Mastermind]]''. By the following day a clip of her giving an incorrect answer to a question about the Swedish climate change activist [[Greta Thunberg]] has been watched more than five million times. When asked to name the teenage activist, Henderson replies with \"Sharon\", a response that prompts Thunberg to change the name on her Twitter account to Sharon in jest, and leads to some online criticism of the actress.<ref name=\"Thunberg\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-50989594 |title=Greta Thunberg changes Twitter name to 'Sharon' after game show error |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=3 January 2020 |accessdate=4 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Seddon |first1=Dan |title=Casualty's Amanda Mealing defends co-star Amanda Henderson over Celebrity Mastermind backlash |url=https://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/casualty/a30389569/casualty-amanda-mealing-defends-amanda-henderson-backlash/ |accessdate=4 January 2020 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=3 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=2|'''4'''\n|[[BBC Two]] airs an evening of programmes dedicated to [[Clive James]], with two editions of ''[[Clive James's Postcard from...]]'' about Sydney and London, and an edition of ''[[Front Row Late]]'' featuring James from 2018.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2020/jan/04/tv-tonight-take-a-peek-behind-the-celebrity-mask |title=TV tonight: take a peek behind the celebrity mask |publisher=Guardian Media Group |newspaper=The Guardian |date=4 January 2020 |accessdate=4 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[The Masked Singer (British TV series)|The Masked Singer]]'', a reality show based on a South Korean [[The Masked Singer|series of the same name]], makes its British television debut on ITV.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2020/jan/04/stars-in-their-eyes-meets-teletubbies-is-the-masked-singer-tvs-weirdest-show |title=Is The Masked Singer TV's weirdest show? |publisher=Guardian Media Group |newspaper=The Guardian |date=4 January 2020 |accessdate=28 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Jeffery |first=Morgan |url=https://www.radiotimes.com/news/tv/2020-01-05/masked-singer-launch-ratings/ |title=The Masked Singer episode 1 ratings \u2013 did it beat The Greatest Dancer? |publisher=Radio Times |date=5 January 2020 |accessdate=28 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|'''5'''\n|''[[Dancing on Ice]]'' returns for a [[Dancing on Ice (series 12)|twelfth series]], and becomes the first UK competitive reality television show to pair a same-sex partnership, with [[Ian \"H\" Watkins]] teaming up with professional ice skater [[Matt Evers]].<ref>{{cite news|first=Laura |last=Martin |url=https://inews.co.uk/culture/television/dancing-on-ice-2020-line-up-cast-contestants-full-when-start-itv-michael-barrymore-quit-636812 |title=Dancing On Ice 2020 line-up: full cast of contestants on the new ITV series after Michael Barrymore quit |publisher=inews |date=2 January 2020 |accessdate=2 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/newsbeat-50835804?intlink_from_url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment_and_arts&link_location=live-reporting-story |title=Dancing On Ice: First same-sex couple don't want to 'be part of a circus' |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=2 January 2020 |accessdate=2 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|'''6'''\n|ITV revamps and extends its breakfast programming. The changes see ''[[Good Morning Britain (2014)|Good Morning Britain]]'' being extended by 30 minutes, running until 9am, with ''[[Lorraine (TV programme)|Lorraine]]'' on air for a full hour, from 9am until 10am. The change removes the historic 9.25am demarcation between breakfast and daytime programming that had existed since breakfast television launched on ITV in 1983.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rxtvlog.com/2019/11/itv-removes-historic-break-in-daytime.html |title=ITV removes historic quirk in major schedule overhaul |date=12 November 2019 |accessdate=6 January 2020 |publisher=RXTV Log}}</ref>\n|-\n|'''8'''\n|The [[Advertising Standards Authority (United Kingdom)|Advertising Standards Authority]] upholds a complaint against ''[[Love Island (British TV series)|Love Island]]'' contestant [[Molly Mae Hague]] over a social media post of her wearing an outfit from an online retailer that was not identifiable as advertising.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/technology-51023274 |title=Love Island star Molly Mae's Insta post banned |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=8 January 2020 |accessdate=8 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|'''10'''\n|[[Samira Ahmed]] wins an equal pay case she brought against the BBC over the difference in pay between herself for presenting ''[[Newswatch (British TV programme)|Newswatch]]'' and [[Jeremy Vine]] for presenting ''[[Points of View (TV programme)|Points of View]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-50599080 |title=Samira Ahmed wins BBC equal pay tribunal |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=10 January 2020 |accessdate=10 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=2|'''12'''\n|BBC Two airs ''Louis Theroux: Selling Sex'', a documentary in which [[Louis Theroux]] examines the world of [[internet prostitution|online sex workers]] in the United Kingdom.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Jenn |last=Selby |url=https://inews.co.uk/culture/television/selling-sex-louis-theroux-new-documentary-when-bbc-two-time-1361442 |title=Everything you need to know about Louis Theroux's new documentary Selling Sex |newspaper==inews |date=10 January 2020 |accessdate=10 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Love Island (2015 TV series)|Love Island]]'' returns to [[ITV2]] for its [[Love Island (2015 TV series, series 6)|sixth series]], with [[Laura Whitmore]] as presenter. Overnight viewing figures indicate the launch episode of what is the first series to be aired in winter is seen by an average audience of 2.51 million; the figure is down 800,000 on the launch episode of the [[Love Island (2015 TV series, series 5)|previous series]] aired in summer 2019.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-51090890 |title=Love Island ratings dip for winter series launch |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=13 January 2020 |accessdate=15 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|'''13'''\n|ITV launches Week 3 of its \"Creates\" Ident package in 2020, designed by Saj Fareed and Asian Women's Resource Centre.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.itv.com/itvcreates/january/saj-fareed-asian-womens-resource-centre |title=Saj Fareed & Asian Women's Resource Centre |publisher=ITV |date=12 January 2020 |accessdate=14 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|'''14'''\n|''Love Island'' contestant Ollie Williams voluntarily leaves the show after less than three days as a participant.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/newsbeat-51108043 |title=Love Island: Ollie Williams quits the villa because he 'loves someone else' |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=14 January 2020 |accessdate=15 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|'''15'''\n|[[Director-General of the BBC|BBC Director-General]] [[Tony Hall, Baron Hall of Birkenhead|Tony Hall]] outlines plans that will see at least two thirds of the BBC's staff based outside London by 2027.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-51118174 |title=BBC boss details more job moves out of London |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=15 January 2020 |accessdate=15 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=3|'''16'''\n|Legislation is drafted before Parliament allowing the use of [[Professional video camera|television cameras]] durin